Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.55,0:00:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our program! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.29,0:00:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the benefits \Nof making the effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.66,0:00:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve \Nin an unassigned territory? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.66,0:00:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Join this family as they travel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.96,0:00:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to a distant area to support \Nthe Kingdom preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.50,0:00:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We will see how such a decision \Nbuilds their faith.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.24,0:00:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And our young ones, \Nhave you started noticing the opposite sex?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.18,0:00:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, you know \Nyou’re not old enough to get married. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.28,0:00:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What can help you to take control \Nof such natural feelings? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We will find out \Nlater in the program.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll also hear the fascinating story \Nof Erich Frost—a brother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.49,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who was sent to a Nazi concentration camp\Nduring World War II because of his faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.76,0:00:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he and his fellow brothers \Nhelp each other to remain faithful? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.20,0:00:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You will find this story \Nvery encouraging.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.14,0:00:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That, and much more, \Nis coming your way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.48,0:01:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on this May program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.80,0:01:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I would first like to read to you \Nsome passages from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.80,0:01:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,found at Ephesians chapter 3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.87,0:01:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 14 through 19. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.94,0:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This will also establish the theme \Nfor my comments this month. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 3, \Nstarting with verse 14, Paul said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.72,0:01:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“For this reason \NI bend my knees to the Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.66,0:01:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“to whom every family in heaven \Nand on earth owes its name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“I pray that he may grant you \Nthrough the abundance of his glory \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.50,0:01:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“to be made mighty \Nin the man you are inside, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.80,0:02:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“with power through his spirit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.07,0:02:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and that through your faith you may have \Nthe Christ dwell in your hearts with love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.78,0:02:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“May you be rooted \Nand established on the foundation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.78,0:02:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“in order that with all the holy ones \Nyou may be thoroughly able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.82,0:02:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“to comprehend fully \Nwhat is the breadth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.59,0:02:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“and length \Nand height and depth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.39,0:02:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to know the love of the Christ, \Nwhich surpasses knowledge, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.99,0:02:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that you may be filled \Nwith all the fullness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.30,0:02:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that God gives.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.57,0:02:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, verse 15 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.57,0:02:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is the inspiration \Nfor my theme, namely, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Glorify Jehovah—The One \Nto Whom Every Family Owes Its Name.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.24,0:02:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The family unit is under a vicious attack \Nin these last days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Insight book \Nlived up to its name \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.39,0:02:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,under the heading “Family.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.99,0:02:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The very insightful comment \Nreads this way: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:03:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“The inspired Scriptures \Nhave foretold a vicious attack \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.80,0:03:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“on the family institution \Nwith a consequent breaking down of morality\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and of human society \Noutside the . . . congregation.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.81,0:03:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The article pointed out \Nthat in “‘the last days’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.48,0:03:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“a condition in which \Ndisobedience to parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.05,0:03:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“disloyalty, and absence \Nof ‘natural affection’ would be rife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,even among those \N‘having a form of godly devotion.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.66,0:03:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How can married couples, \Nparents, and children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.20,0:03:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,counteract \Nsuch a diabolical attack? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember those verses \Nwe read in Ephesians chapter 3? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.27,0:03:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 16 said that the One \Nto whom every family owes its name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, would ‘grant us\Nto be made mighty\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.61,0:03:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the person we are inside.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.88,0:03:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah can give us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.79,0:03:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the internal \Nspiritual strength to fight back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.52,0:04:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,against Satan’s efforts \Nto destroy the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.19,0:04:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.19,0:04:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,By being immersed in God’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, \Nby imitating the loving way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.57,0:04:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus treated his disciples. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.27,0:04:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you note \Nthat Ephesians 3:17 said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.14,0:04:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we are to “have the Christ \Ndwell in [our] hearts with love”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.35,0:04:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, if each of us cherishes \Nthe Christ in our hearts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.15,0:04:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to the point that he dwells, \Nor resides, there constantly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,our family \Nwill not only survive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but it will truly thrive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.39,0:04:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be so evident \Nthat verse 17 further states \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.53,0:04:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will “be rooted \Nand established on the foundation.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.67,0:04:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be solid! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.21,0:04:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And keep in mind \Nthat 1 Corinthians 3:11 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.08,0:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that the “foundation” \Non which we build \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.01,0:04:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“is Jesus Christ.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.45,0:05:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then verse 18 \Nof Ephesians chapter 3 indicates that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.02,0:05:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual peripheral vision \Nwill be enhanced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.06,0:05:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not \Nhave spiritual blind spots \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that could allow the spirit of the world \Nto creep into the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.06,0:05:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That verse says \Nthat we will “be thoroughly able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.60,0:05:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“to comprehend fully \Nwhat is the breadth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and length \Nand height and depth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All aspects of Jesus’ personality \Nwill come into play \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we interact \Nwith family members. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.58,0:05:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, verse 19 \Nsums up the result when it says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.92,0:05:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that we would then \Nhave come “to know the love of the Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.59,0:05:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which surpasses knowledge.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.92,0:05:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Granted, \Nknowledge is important, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is the application \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of Christlike love \Nthat will preserve our family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.70,0:05:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping it vibrantly intact.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Family life \Nin these critical last days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.18,0:06:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,could be likened to those \Nwho suffer from diabetes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.48,0:06:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is believed \Nthat diabetes is caused \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,by both genetic \Nand environmental factors. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.02,0:06:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, all in the family \Nhave inherited sin \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.09,0:06:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and imperfection \Nfrom our first human parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.89,0:06:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Adam and Eve, \Nas if genetically. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.69,0:06:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we are also exposed \Nto the ever more toxic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.17,0:06:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,environmental factors \Nof Satan’s evil world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.57,0:06:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Most who suffer \Nfrom a serious case of diabetes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,need to use two methods \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.14,0:06:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to successfully relieve the symptoms \Nand lead a normal life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to watch their diet \Nand, in many cases, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.85,0:06:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,take an injection \Nof insulin daily.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually, \Nwe need to avoid the sickly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.36,0:06:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,sweet junk food \Nthat the world promotes in movies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.49,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,talk shows, \Nthe Internet, and in print. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:06:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as with the person \Nwho has diabetes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.94,0:07:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,this requires \Na permanent lifestyle change \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.87,0:07:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from what we might have \Nexposed ourselves to in the past. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to avoiding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,unwholesome junk food \Nfrom Satan’s system,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we also need \Nto take daily “injections” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s Word \Nand other wholesome provisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.69,0:07:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This has become more \Nand more important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the deeper we get \Ninto these last days.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.63,0:07:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How has our organization provided this \Nwhen it comes to family life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the early 1900’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the focus was on preaching \Nthe good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Little attention was given \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.84,0:07:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to building strong \NChristian marriages and families. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For a time, \Nmarriage was even discouraged \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.25,0:07:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,well beyond \Nthe intent of the Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I did some checking, \Nand commendably \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,between 1919 and 1921 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.36,0:07:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a feature \Nin the Golden Age magazine\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.23,0:08:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,once or twice a month \Ncalled the “Juvenile Bible Study.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.70,0:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1920, \Na brochure was released \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,called The Golden Age ABC. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it wasn’t until 1941 \Nthat the now famous book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.71,0:08:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled Children was handed out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.98,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to all young ones \Nat the convention that year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the last days progressed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.12,0:08:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more information\Nfor families was produced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.25,0:08:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in the 1970’s, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the book Making Your Family Life Happy \Nwas released. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.86,0:08:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,About the same time, \Nthe books Listening to the Great Teacher \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and Your Youth—Getting the Best out of It \Nwere published. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1982, Awake! \Nbegan a regular series \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that has run for decades \Nentitled “Young People Ask.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.61,0:08:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have two up-to-date books \Nwith the same title, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.95,0:08:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the series of articles \Ncontinues on the jw.org website. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.89,0:08:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the book \NLearn From the Great Teacher \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.86,0:09:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and so many features \Nand activities for young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.19,0:09:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on the website that I would be out of time \Nif I tried to enumerate them all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.13,0:09:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There are also regular articles \Nin our magazines \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.47,0:09:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,about marriage \Nand family life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will certainly never forget \Nthe privilege I had in 2012 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to introduce the animated series \NBecome Jehovah’s Friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.55,0:09:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That has proved \Nto be a blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.88,0:09:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for both young ones \Nand their parents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.09,0:09:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What a teaching tool for both!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2014, I attended \Nthe international convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.43,0:09:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in Atlanta, Georgia, \Nhere in the United States. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.10,0:09:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,After a little two-year-old girl \Nsaw my face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on the big jumbo screen \Ngiving a talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.44,0:09:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,she eagerly started searching \Nall around her for someone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When her parents asked her \Nwho she was looking for, she said, “Caleb. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.65,0:10:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He must be here because I saw \Nhis grandfather giving a talk.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Many children ask \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.72,0:10:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet Caleb in person \Nwhen they visit Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Two postings \Nof an item every month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.73,0:10:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is making quite an impression \Non little hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.20,0:10:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With Bible principles \Nbeing impressed on the minds and hearts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of children so early, \Nwe prayerfully anticipate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.61,0:10:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,many spiritually-minded teenagers \Nin the years to come.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We have so much \Nhealthy spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.88,0:10:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for counteracting \Nfamily “diabetes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For this, \Nwe give all glory to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the one “to whom \Nevery family . . . owes its name.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.09,0:10:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the favorite passages \Nof Scripture that anyone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.10,0:10:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,professing to be Christian \Nloves is the 23rd Psalm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.03,0:10:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Family heads, can we benefit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.97,0:10:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,from imitating not only \Nthe Fine Shepherd, Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but also the Great Shepherd, \NJehovah God? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to borrow \Nthe text of the 23rd Psalm \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.72,0:11:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and adjust the words so that we \Ncan sense a family’s tranquillity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.65,0:11:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when headship \Nis exercised properly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.66,0:11:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you husbands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.79,0:11:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as the script is read, \Nimagine it is your wife’s voice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.53,0:11:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,describing the effect \Nyour headship has on your family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.87,0:11:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘[My husband] \Nis [our] shepherd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘[We] will lack nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.28,0:11:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘In grassy pastures \N[refreshing recreation] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.22,0:11:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‘he makes [us] lie down; \Nhe leads [us] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‘to well-watered resting-places \N[meetings and conventions]. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.49,0:11:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He refreshes [us]. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,‘He leads [us in the ministry] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.70,0:11:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘in the paths of righteousness \Nfor the sake of [Jehovah’s] name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.23,0:12:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Though [we] walk in the valley \Nof deep [economic] shadow, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.87,0:12:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‘[we] fear no harm, \Nfor [Dad is] with [us]; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‘your rod and your staff \N[loving discipline] reassure [us]. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.61,0:12:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You prepare a table [of family worship, \Nhelping the children] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.62,0:12:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‘for [us] before [our] enemies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.89,0:12:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You refresh \N[our] head[s] with oil; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.86,0:12:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‘[Our] cup \N[of family well-being] is well-filled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.26,0:12:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Surely goodness and loyal love \Nwill pursue [our family] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.60,0:12:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,‘all the days of [our] life, \Nand [our family] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.33,0:12:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will dwell in the house \Nof Jehovah for all [our] days.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.71,0:12:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No further application called for. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel the sense of security \Nthat envelops \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.65,0:12:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the interior rooms \Nof such a home, don’t we?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.19,0:12:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember \Nthe point made \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.92,0:12:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in Ephesians chapter 3, \Nwhich we read earlier? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:12:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We are to treasure \NJesus’ personality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.56,0:13:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and let it “dwell” \Nin our hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If all in the family \Nmake a determined effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to treat each other \Nlike Jesus would, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we can conquer the world! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we—His spiritual family \Nin heaven \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.74,0:13:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and all humans on earth \Nwho dedicate their lives to Him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.28,0:13:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,—give glory to Jehovah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, we thank Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.49,0:13:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for all the spiritual provisions \Nhe has made through his Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.29,0:13:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and organization to protect every family \Nwho takes up his name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah bless \Nall of you families \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.43,0:13:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as you strive to win \Nthe war that Satan wages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.77,0:13:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,against you \Nin these last days.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.64,0:13:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,An important aspect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of keeping \Nthe family’s spiritual health intact \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is by making full use \Nof the Family Worship arrangement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.42,0:13:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \Npay attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to how the family head \Nis aware of the needs of the family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.96,0:14:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he plans accordingly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.56,0:14:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, my name is Joe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.03,0:14:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A few weeks ago, \Nwe all sat together for supper. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.97,0:14:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so tired, and my wife, \NJenny, felt the same way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.44,0:14:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,She always does it all, \Ntaking care of the children so well, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was not easy \Nfor her in recent weeks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sarah felt that we are too restrictive \Non how she dresses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.55,0:14:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She just does not understand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.68,0:14:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard to convince her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.82,0:14:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And to motivate her \Nto share in the field service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.35,0:14:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is becoming a challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.36,0:14:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was not always like this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She used to enjoy \Ngoing out in field service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.93,0:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And Tom, \Nhe is such a good boy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but all of a sudden, \Nhe was raving about the games \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,his classmates \Nhave on their phones. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s always \Nabout having supernatural powers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.47,0:14:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it fascinated him, \Neven though he is small. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.74,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I asked him \Nto take out the garbage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.41,0:15:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly \Nhis superpowers left him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.02,0:15:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And Mike, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our smallest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.59,0:15:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it was hard \Nto get him to go to bed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or clean up his room. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.93,0:15:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized there are a few things \Nwe need to speak about.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.70,0:15:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Joe came to me, and we talked \Na lot about our children that same evening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.24,0:15:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We wondered, \N‘What would be the best for them?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.74,0:15:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we had an idea!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The following day \Nwe asked our children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.92,0:15:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if we could consider Noah \Nas the theme for our next family worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.65,0:15:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us liked the idea. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of us \Nshould prepare something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.19,0:15:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mike, Tom, and I \Nwanted to build the ark.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.87,0:15:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, \Nwe need the animals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Sarah \Nshould collect pictures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.38,0:16:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for the story \Nfrom our publications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.25,0:16:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had to take time \Nto think again about the story of Noah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.39,0:16:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it \Ncan help our family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.72,0:16:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jenny and Sarah were responsible \Nfor the wardrobe and food.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,While preparing, \NI got the chance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.46,0:16:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak with Sarah about her dress \Nin a more relaxed setting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She understood that, \Nlike Noah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to Jehovah’s commands, \Nwe need to do “just so.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.91,0:16:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the evening arrived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about \Nhow it was before the Flood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.85,0:16:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and what kind of world \NNoah and his family lived in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Noah’s family needed \Nreal courage to preach. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.76,0:16:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to explain about the rain \Nand how the ark would be needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.09,0:16:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive the Flood\N—something that had never happened before.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.86,0:17:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people \Nthought they were crazy! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And while we were talking \Nabout this, it came out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that Sarah felt embarrassed when she met \Na schoolmate in the field service recently.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.98,0:17:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized Noah must have felt \Nthe same as me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet, \Nhe was so courageous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.62,0:17:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad read Genesis 6:9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.75,0:17:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Noah walked with the true God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.89,0:17:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So he could have every confidence \Nin his Friend, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be just like that!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.36,0:17:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For Tom, \NI found a great picture.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.93,0:17:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad told us that the world \Nat this time was very bad. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,People were fighting \Nand many were afraid, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.34,0:17:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is why \NJehovah brought the Flood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.01,0:17:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me think \Nabout the games from my schoolmates. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.28,0:17:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I like to play those games, \Nbut I know that Jehovah does not like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.35,0:17:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So why do I?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.65,0:17:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best part \Nwas when we got inside the ark!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.73,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I read Genesis 6:19: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“And bring into the ark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.73,0:18:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,two of every sort \Nof living creature.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad showed us \Nhow the animals went into the ark. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one had its own place, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.97,0:18:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and they went inside \Ntwo at a time without any chaos.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.71,0:18:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I explained that we also need \Nto keep our rooms clean like the ark. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.52,0:18:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw that Mike got the point. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted \Nto keep in mind Genesis 6:22:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.62,0:18:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Noah did according to all \Nthat God had commanded him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He did just so.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.27,0:18:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the rain came, \Nbut we survived! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.70,0:18:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.70,0:18:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We all realized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.97,0:18:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Noah also must have been \Ntired sometimes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but he never gave up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.04,0:18:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a good lesson for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.05,0:18:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We must take care \Nof our family as Noah did, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.05,0:18:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,also by having \Na regular family worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.39,0:19:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like this.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.79,0:19:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That example really showed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.93,0:19:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,many of the great benefits \Nof family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to the obvious\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.73,0:19:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—coming together to learn \Nmore about our heavenly Father\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.20,0:19:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—we saw how family worship \Ngave the daughter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.14,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,an opportunity \Nto open up about matters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that had been bothering her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.68,0:19:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And thanks to the good work \Nof the parents,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the children \Nlearned something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.95,0:19:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they could apply \Nin their daily lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve now invited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister Ortiz \Nfrom New Britain, Connecticut, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit our studio. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Ortiz serves as an elder \Nand as a regular pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.26,0:19:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s had many additional privileges \Nof service over the years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.60,0:19:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And Linnette has been regular pioneering \Nfor over six years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.40,0:19:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the reason we wanted \Nto talk with them is that thus far \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.28,0:19:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they have successfully countered \NSatan’s attacks on their family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d like to hear \Nhow they accomplished this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.48,0:20:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, Freddie, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.49,0:20:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,tell us a little bit \Nabout your family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.89,0:20:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither Linnette nor I \Nwere raised in the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.96,0:20:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we met, \Nand we fell in love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.89,0:20:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \Nmarriage was not for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.70,0:20:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So we started \Na romantic relationship for two years \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,before we started attending \Nthe first meeting at the Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon thereafter, \Nwe started studying the Bible; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.97,0:20:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we took two studies per week; \Nwe knew this was the truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.51,0:20:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But also we learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah sees immorality, \Nso we needed to do some changes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.78,0:20:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Linnette’s parents \Nwanted her to continue \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with her education, \Nso we needed to change our behavior. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So two years after, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we did the changes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.33,0:20:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one \Nbecause we did love Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.80,0:20:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Number two because we loved \Nwhat we were learning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was worth it \Nto follow Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So two years later, \Nwe got married \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:21:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we got baptized\N—and we got married.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.54,0:21:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Linnette, you were raised \Nwithout a knowledge of Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What changes did you both \Nhave to make to ensure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.62,0:21:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your own family \Nwould have a fine foundation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.69,0:21:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and be successful?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.69,0:21:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, prior to our baptism, \NFreddie had a serious drinking problem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.16,0:21:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And based on the way we were raised, \Nthere was a lot of jealousy going on\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and, I would say, a lack of confidence \Nand trust in each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.60,0:21:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My Bible teacher, \Nthankfully, suggested to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.47,0:21:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to study the book \NMaking Your Family Life Happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.01,0:21:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we ended up studying \Nthat book twice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That publication and the Bible principles \Nin it became the foundation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of our wonderful marriage \Nand the happy family we enjoy today.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.09,0:21:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Freddie, maybe you \Ncan tell us about your children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.96,0:21:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they are doing \Nwith their lives now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.96,0:21:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We have two sons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.43,0:21:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabriel, he’s the oldest one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.43,0:21:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He started regular pioneering \Nwhen he was 14 years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.43,0:22:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At 18, he was appointed \Nas a ministerial servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At 22 years old, he has been working \Nin the Plumbing Department \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.31,0:22:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Warwick construction \Nfor more than two years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.51,0:22:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrian is now 18 years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.71,0:22:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And he also started \Nregular pioneering when he was 14. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.45,0:22:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, he handles \Nthe accounts for the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.09,0:22:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and other privileges as well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.76,0:22:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they both have had \Nan early start in their theocratic careers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.36,0:22:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s commendable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.03,0:22:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’re both \Nproud of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.03,0:22:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re confident \Nthat Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.43,0:22:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the One “to whom \Nevery family . . . owes its name,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.24,0:22:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is pleased that they are giving \Nan answer to his taunter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.17,0:22:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition \Nto the Family Life book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.04,0:22:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what else contributed \Nto the success your family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.48,0:22:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,has experienced, Linnette?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.48,0:22:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body has provided us \Nwith so many publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.29,0:22:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with direction for families, \Nof course, all based on Jehovah’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.89,0:23:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So we decided early on that whenever \Na question or an issue came up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.76,0:23:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we would not make \Nany decision based on impulse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.03,0:23:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we would research it \Nin the publications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.37,0:23:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray to Jehovah \Nfor him to give us wisdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.11,0:23:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we even pray \Nfor him to guide us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.31,0:23:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the right time to talk \Nto each other or to counsel the boys. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.61,0:23:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always heard \Nthat there are stages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.22,0:23:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the child’s life \Nand personality development. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I researched in advance \Nas to what to expect. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.96,0:23:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In that way, \Nwe were not surprised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.69,0:23:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when we saw changes \Nin attitudes or ideas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.50,0:23:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that helped us \Nrealize what needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to be addressed or corrected \Nas opposed to what was normal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.17,0:23:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for that stage \Nin the boys’ lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.18,0:23:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Very practical. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.44,0:23:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Freddie, \Nwhat can you add?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years, I have learned \Nhow essential it is to become a good listener\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.98,0:23:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—also understanding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.72,0:23:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell my family \Nhow much I love them every day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because we never know \Nwhen circumstances might change. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.42,0:24:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Family worship \Nis very important for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it is easy to put off, \Nbut the benefits are hard to beat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.76,0:24:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, \Nbefore this arrangement started, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.97,0:24:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we as a family, we valued \Nthe Bible study with the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.04,0:24:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that a fetus \Nthat is six months, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.11,0:24:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,he can recognize \Nthe family’s voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.71,0:24:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So I started a Bible study with my sons \Nwhen they were still in the womb . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.85,0:24:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that nice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.12,0:24:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . and continued \Nto do so after that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.46,0:24:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that secular work \Nand other activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.39,0:24:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,can block \Na regular program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.46,0:24:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but we need to fight that tendency \Nif we want to succeed in family worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.00,0:24:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.00,0:24:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems your efforts \Npaid off when we consider \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.34,0:24:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,how well your family \Nhas done spiritually \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.74,0:24:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the close relationship \Nyou have with each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.65,0:25:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Linnette, \Nit sounds as if the family is perfect\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.35,0:25:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—no challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.78,0:25:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the case?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.79,0:25:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.79,0:25:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First Corinthians 10:13 says \Nthat Christians will face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.39,0:25:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,challenges \Nthat are “common to [all] men.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.53,0:25:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have faced the normal challenges \Nthat come with raising a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.47,0:25:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The same verse indicates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.77,0:25:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that if we do things \NJehovah’s way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.91,0:25:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we may increase the opportunity \Nfor him to “make the way out” for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.78,0:25:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One unexpected challenge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.78,0:25:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that has changed \Nour family dynamics \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.08,0:25:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,over the years now, \Nwas when Freddie \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.69,0:25:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was diagnosed \Nwith cancer in 2012. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.89,0:25:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The treatment was aggressive \Nand took its toll on his health. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.56,0:25:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Our whole lifestyle changed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.56,0:25:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to move out \Nfrom our house . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.10,0:25:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . to an apartment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.14,0:25:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we gave away our dog, Spike, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.30,0:26:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have to watch our expenses \Nreally closely to keep going. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.75,0:26:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This could have put a lot \Nof strain in our family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.58,0:26:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in our marriage, \Nand in our spirituality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.65,0:26:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But, again, by praying to Jehovah constantly\Nand applying Bible principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.39,0:26:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can say my marriage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.73,0:26:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and my family \Nhave never been better.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.73,0:26:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.86,0:26:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritually, we kept our routine, \Nand we all stayed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.03,0:26:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in full-time service \Nthroughout the ordeal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.84,0:26:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The boys \Nhave cooperated very well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.11,0:26:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They have offered \Nto work to give us money. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.11,0:26:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But we prefer for them \Nto keep focused on the Kingdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.91,0:26:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are confident \Nthat Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.25,0:26:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,will add on \Nto the things we need. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.32,0:26:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Freddie has been \Na great example for all of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.39,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because he pushes himself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.46,0:26:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep his spiritual routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.53,0:26:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You never see him \Ncomplaining or in a bad mood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.87,0:27:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that has been very inspiring \Nfor the rest of the family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.34,0:27:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, that is quite a story. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.74,0:27:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You folks will certainly relate \Nto the convention drama video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.71,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that was advertised \Non our April program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.38,0:27:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Freddie, we’re very sorry to hear \Nabout your physical condition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.85,0:27:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any \Nfavorite scriptures that you use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.72,0:27:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to help keep you going spiritually \Nand to stay strong?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.79,0:27:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.33,0:27:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to mention a few, \NPhilippians 4:6,7 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.03,0:27:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,has been my life since 2012, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.90,0:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where I have to pray \Nto Jehovah constantly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.97,0:27:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he can give me \Nthe strength that I need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.17,0:27:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome my health. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.44,0:27:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, \NPhilippians says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.85,0:27:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that he will give us \Npeace of mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.18,0:27:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, \Nhe will safeguard our heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.49,0:27:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s something \NI’ve been seeing from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.29,0:27:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Isaiah 41:10 states: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.83,0:28:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious, \Nfor I am your God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.03,0:28:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Those words give me comfort \Nthat he will keep on helping us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.63,0:28:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in these different circumstances \Nin our life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.87,0:28:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I do understand that my wife has a lot \Nof responsibilities in the household,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.74,0:28:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so I had to reread \NProverbs 31 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.41,0:28:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 10 to 31, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.28,0:28:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where it describes \Nall of the responsibility a good wife \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.42,0:28:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,might have to shoulder \Nfor the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.29,0:28:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So Brother Morris, \Nshe is my Proverbs 31 wife!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.42,0:28:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A good wife for sure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.43,0:28:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve obviously shown how much \Nyou love and respect each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.30,0:28:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s commendable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.30,0:28:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And your focus on being the best parents \Nyou could be is a good example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.70,0:28:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for parents viewing \Nthe program at this time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.01,0:28:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This will come \Nas a surprise to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.14,0:28:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but we would like to invite your two sons \Nout to see what they remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.98,0:28:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,from growing up \Nin the family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have Gabriel \Nand Adrian with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.79,0:29:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom’s getting a little teary-eyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.26,0:29:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s understandable. \NIt was a surprise, see. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.40,0:29:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So Gabriel, \Nsince you’re the oldest, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.77,0:29:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we will start with you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.24,0:29:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you remember \Nabout your family life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.77,0:29:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,first in Puerto Rico \Nand later here in the United States?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.51,0:29:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember faithfully going \Nto all the meetings and going out in service\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.02,0:29:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,every Saturday\N—that was just the routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.22,0:29:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In Puerto Rico, \Nmy dad had to work a lot though, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.22,0:29:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and like he said before, \Nthat’s easy to get in the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.26,0:29:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of a good family worship routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.86,0:29:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can honestly say that once we made \Nthat transition of moving over here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.07,0:29:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that helped us to have \Na good family worship routine, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.27,0:29:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has helped us \Nto get closer and closer each day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.71,0:29:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, isn’t that nice?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.01,0:29:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Adrian, anything you can add \Nabout the homelife?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.04,0:29:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, my mom \Nand dad have always \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.35,0:30:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,shown a great love for Jehovah \Nbut also for each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.22,0:30:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So as kids, \Nyou could just sense that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.95,0:30:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So love and respect \Nis what we’ve always known. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.16,0:30:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now that my brother and I are older, \Nwe have a great bond with each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.76,0:30:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We love each other and we can tell \Neach other everything about our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.10,0:30:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s due to that love \Nand respect that they have shown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.57,0:30:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if there are disagreements, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.64,0:30:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which there are always going \Nto be disagreements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.64,0:30:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because it’s an imperfect family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.64,0:30:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but that love is always there \Nto bridge those differences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.51,0:30:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I also would like to add, \Nsomething that helped me a lot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.65,0:30:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was a routine \Nthat my dad and I had \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.72,0:30:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right before going to school; \Nwe would always read the daily text. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.92,0:30:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would always say, “Behave, \Nand remember that Jehovah loves you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.16,0:30:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think he knows \Nhow much that really helped me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.73,0:30:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,go through \Neveryday challenges at school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s priceless. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.93,0:30:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, very nice observations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.84,0:31:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabriel, I’m interested \Nin understanding what prompted you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.38,0:31:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to regular pioneer \Nwhen you were only 14 years old?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.25,0:31:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was at a point \Nwhere my dad lost his job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.92,0:31:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than stressing about it\N—worrying about it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.42,0:31:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,—he looked at things \Nwith a spiritual perspective. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.09,0:31:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So he started to pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.09,0:31:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And since our schedules \Nmatched perfectly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.16,0:31:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was his little pioneer buddy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.16,0:31:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I would go out in service \Nwith him whenever he needed it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.90,0:31:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel like if spiritual families, \Nyou know, focus on spiritual matters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.77,0:31:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it helps them \Nto become closer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.90,0:31:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can’t imagine \Nhow our relationship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.77,0:31:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and respect for one another \Ncan be any better than what it is now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.78,0:31:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.65,0:31:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Adrian, \Nyou began pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.42,0:31:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when you were 14 as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.42,0:31:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you think \Nthat affected you as a person?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.35,0:31:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, first of all, \Nthe reason why I started pioneering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.36,0:31:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was because I was going out in service \Nwith the rest of my family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.56,0:31:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and since they were already pioneering, \NI was getting the time in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do think \Nthat taking on the responsibility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.63,0:32:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting \Nat least 70 hours a month \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.97,0:32:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the service \Ndoes make you think differently \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.51,0:32:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at 14 than it would have otherwise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.58,0:32:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it has helped me \Nmature spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.78,0:32:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has contributed to me being used \Nto my full potential in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.55,0:32:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And honestly, I wouldn’t trade it \Nfor anything, well, maybe going to Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.55,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabriel, back to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.96,0:32:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us what was it like \Nwhen you learned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.36,0:32:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that your dad \Nhad a serious health problem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.10,0:32:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and would not be able to provide \Nfor the family like he used to?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.23,0:32:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That was probably one \Nof the biggest challenges I have ever faced.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.04,0:32:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When my dad got diagnosed with cancer, \Nit was about the same time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.97,0:32:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that I got my call to Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.04,0:32:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was torn; I was divided. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.58,0:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like if I was to go \Nto Bethel now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.18,0:32:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be selfish of me \Nto leave my family at a time like that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.39,0:32:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But my family \Nalways had a spiritual view \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.26,0:32:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on things and cited scriptures \Nlike Matthew 6:33 constantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.96,0:33:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It helped me to see as a whole—as a family\N—we put Kingdom interests first; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.03,0:33:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah \Nwas going to provide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.03,0:33:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because he’s a loving father \Nand friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.64,0:33:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then my dad lost his job, \Nand again all these feelings came up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.97,0:33:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But my family was adamant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.18,0:33:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They let me know that the congregation \Nhad been taking care of them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.08,0:33:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for months now, \Nand then doing some simplifying \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.32,0:33:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,on their own \Nhelped them as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.45,0:33:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn’t have to worry \Nabout anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.52,0:33:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know that there’s a scripture that says\Nthat we’ve got to take care of our own. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.59,0:33:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So I do anything I can \Nto help my family back home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.53,0:33:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I hope \Nis that I can have a good faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.40,0:33:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,like they’ve shown \Nthrough these difficult times.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.77,0:33:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank all of you \Nfor joining us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.24,0:33:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think all of us \Nare feeling that emotion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.11,0:33:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel very close \Nto you for sharing that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.65,0:33:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as a father, I can appreciate \Nall that Freddie is trying to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.72,0:34:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as head of the family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.25,0:34:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And, Linnette, your support \Nbeyond normal \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.16,0:34:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is very much \Nto be commended. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.76,0:34:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can tell your family \Nis thriving spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.03,0:34:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and we pray Jehovah \Nwill continue to bless your efforts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.50,0:34:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,come what may. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.50,0:34:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thank you, \NGabriel and Adrian, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.77,0:34:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for your surprise \Nto the studio. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.64,0:34:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much \Nfor taking the time to be interviewed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.31,0:34:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the privilege.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.01,0:34:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for the privilege.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.65,0:34:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.28,0:34:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As we just learned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.78,0:34:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,an excellent way of maintaining \Nthe spirituality of the family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.42,0:34:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is by spending quality time \Ntogether in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.56,0:34:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We would now like to introduce you \Nto a family from Russia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.03,0:34:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They traveled far away \Nto work together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.10,0:34:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in unassigned territory \Nin Siberia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.44,0:34:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Their experience confirms \Nhow spiritual activities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.41,0:34:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,not only build up our faith \Nbut can also bring our family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.01,0:35:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to each other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.45,0:35:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We are traveling \Nto a very interesting territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.92,0:35:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It is on the shores \Nof Lake Baikal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.39,0:35:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,From where we live, \Nit is 600 kilometers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.60,0:35:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have so many memories \Nto take home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.00,0:35:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The scenery is always stunning \Nin all types of weather.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.31,0:35:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here there are beautiful cliffs \Nand valleys.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.58,0:35:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We cross \Nseveral mountain passes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.75,0:35:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we go by ferry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.12,0:35:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt very strange \Nbeing in the car while crossing the river.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.79,0:35:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When we have the opportunity, \Nwe witness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.19,0:35:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to people \Nwe meet on the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.99,0:35:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do sincere people \Ntrust the Holy Scriptures? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.30,0:35:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have a look \Nat what it says here: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.77,0:35:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“All scripture is inspired of God.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.47,0:36:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We usually serve \Nin isolated territory for a week or more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.84,0:36:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have come to the same place \Nwhere we were last year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.48,0:36:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so we already know \Na lot about it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.68,0:36:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Living in a tent \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.72,0:36:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is very different \Nfrom living in the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.45,0:36:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we don’t have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.45,0:36:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,any conveniences, \Nlike a toilet or a shower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.02,0:36:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The only place to wash \Nis in Lake Baikal, which is freezing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.76,0:36:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This simple life \Nis like an adventure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.47,0:36:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As we have quite a big group\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.24,0:36:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—there are 12 of us\N—we have also organized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.41,0:36:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.44,0:36:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We consider \Nthe daily text together and take part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.75,0:36:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in discussing our publications \Nusing the questions.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.48,0:36:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a friendly, \Nrelaxed atmosphere. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.59,0:36:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody enjoys it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.59,0:36:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our isolated territory, \Nwhere we are preaching, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.03,0:36:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is a rural area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.13,0:36:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we don’t have \Nany prepared maps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.40,0:36:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we have our meetings \Nfor field service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.07,0:37:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we divide up, \Nall taking different streets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.97,0:37:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We also think \Nabout what clothes to wear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.97,0:37:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Experience has shown \Nthat our clothes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.31,0:37:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us \Nto win over these people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.41,0:37:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we try to dress simply. \NWe don’t wear ties.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.79,0:37:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The people there are kind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.76,0:37:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they even invite us in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.49,0:37:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We can have discussions \Nwith some of them—sometimes long ones.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.30,0:37:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There you meet \Nmore receptive people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.67,0:37:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,than unresponsive ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.50,0:37:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and that really is encouraging. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.80,0:37:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes you just want \Nto keep on preaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.07,0:37:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,without stopping.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.71,0:37:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The trips have helped \Nour son make spiritual progress. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.31,0:37:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For us as his parents, \Nthat is the greatest blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.32,0:37:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.32,0:37:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,after one of these trips, \Nhe became an unbaptized publisher.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.96,0:37:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This territory is different \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.39,0:38:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from what I am used to, \Nso I was worried. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.59,0:38:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know \Nwhat sort of people lived there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.80,0:38:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or what their attitude \Nwas toward Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.87,0:38:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But after praying when knocking \Non the first door, my fear disappeared. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.81,0:38:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to place 270 tracts.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.14,0:38:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,While we were witnessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.01,0:38:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we showed the people \Nthe addresses in our publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.55,0:38:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could write \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.82,0:38:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if they found\Nwhat they had read interesting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.15,0:38:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We usually start witnessing \Nabout 12 noon, and we finish \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.09,0:38:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,around 5:00 p.m. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.93,0:38:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the relaxation part \Nof our day begins.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.60,0:38:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a campfire, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.60,0:38:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,some games, \Nsome music, and fun.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.61,0:38:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Early in the day, \Nwe used our energy in the ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.21,0:38:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and afterward we were able \Nto relax and enjoy each other’s company.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:38:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we combine \Nboth our ministry and relaxation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.02,0:39:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the delights \Nof these trips is the fish\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.19,0:39:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—the famous Baikal omul.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.76,0:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,These trips really strengthen \Nthe unity in our family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.60,0:39:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We really have \Ndrawn closer together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.20,0:39:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It is invigorating \Nand enriches us spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.71,0:39:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We experience \Npure joy from knowing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.81,0:39:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah \Nhas blessed our efforts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.91,0:39:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel like we have our batteries \Ncharged for the entire year.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.52,0:39:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It is very encouraging to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.73,0:39:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,such a spiritually focused family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.69,0:39:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice \Nthat it was after one such trip \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.83,0:39:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that their son \Nbecame an unbaptized publisher? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.37,0:39:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure that brought \Nmuch joy to his parents.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.64,0:39:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you interested \Nin a preaching assignment\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.64,0:39:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in territory seldom worked? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.84,0:40:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, form a group \Nof no more than 20 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.18,0:40:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask the elders \Nin your congregation for further instructions\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.92,0:40:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and an Application \Nfor Territory Seldom Worked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.52,0:40:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you have filled out the form, \Nthe Congregation Service Committee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.93,0:40:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,will review it and submit it \Nto your local branch.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.06,0:40:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Theocratic activities, \Nsuch as family worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.94,0:40:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,spending time in the ministry together, \Nalong with balanced amounts of recreation,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.94,0:40:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can truly fortify our family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.28,0:40:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw in the interview \Nwith the Ortiz family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.68,0:40:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,such spiritual preparation \Nhelps us when we face challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.55,0:40:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \Na family followed Scriptural counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.49,0:40:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when they faced the challenge \Nof having to relocate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.23,0:40:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to another city.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.40,0:40:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For 23 years, \Nwe’ve called this place home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.54,0:40:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve raised a family here\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.87,0:41:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—two beautiful girls.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.11,0:41:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months ago, \Nmy boss called me into his office. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.05,0:41:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The company was restructuring. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.58,0:41:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They valued my work, \Nbut if I wanted to keep my job, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.42,0:41:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I would need to move. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.95,0:41:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a difficult decision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.79,0:41:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My job allowed me to support my family well,\Nand it had never interfered \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.13,0:41:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with our spiritual routine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.40,0:41:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We said many prayers about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.63,0:41:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We discussed it as a family, \Nand we decided to move. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.24,0:41:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But we were anxious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.54,0:41:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My family has only ever known \None home, one congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.21,0:41:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My girls have many friends \Nin the congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.31,0:41:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,good examples who are helping them \Nto serve Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.95,0:41:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going \Nto be hard on all of us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.75,0:41:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A brother in our hall had moved \Ninto the congregation a few years ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.76,0:41:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him how his family \Ncoped with the challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.36,0:42:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the key to staying grounded \Nis maintaining the one thing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.03,0:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that should never change \N—our spiritual routine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.94,0:42:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But that requires \Nwork and planning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.94,0:42:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure our move doesn’t stop us \Nfrom getting to the meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.68,0:42:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing in the ministry, \Nspending time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.05,0:42:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with our brothers and sisters, \Nand looking after our family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.48,0:42:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,His advice was spot-on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.89,0:42:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,After some research, I found a scripture \Nthat illustrated our situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.79,0:42:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the rain poured down \Nand the floods came \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.93,0:42:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the winds blew and lashed \Nagainst that house, but it did not cave in, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.73,0:42:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for it had been founded on the rock.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.64,0:42:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The discreet man \Nbuilt his house on good foundations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.58,0:42:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a plan, \Nand he worked hard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.48,0:42:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When the storm came, \Nhis house survived.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.68,0:42:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As a family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.05,0:42:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we needed a plan that would help us \Nstay spiritually grounded through our move. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.59,0:42:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wrote our own plan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.69,0:43:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the discreet man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.86,0:43:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to build our move \Non a strong spiritual foundation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.33,0:43:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we made a visit \Nto our new congregation ahead of our move.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.80,0:43:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the years, \Nit becomes a comfort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.37,0:43:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to walk into a Kingdom Hall \Nand see familiar faces. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.58,0:43:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Walking into our new congregation \Nreminded me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.85,0:43:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how much we are going \Nto miss everyone.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.52,0:43:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Bible tells us \Nthat ‘with the measure we measure out, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.29,0:43:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,others will measure \Nto us in return.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.06,0:43:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we resolved \Nto show love first.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.13,0:43:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, I’m Jessica.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.77,0:43:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I’m Samantha. \NNice to meet you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.60,0:43:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The best way to get to know \Nour new congregation is to work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.91,0:43:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with the brothers \Nand sisters in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.51,0:43:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where we go, \Nwe’ll find people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.24,0:43:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that love Jehovah \Nand each other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.95,0:43:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving day finally arrived. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.28,0:43:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The last boxes were packed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.29,0:44:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We locked the door one final time \Nand began our journey to our new home.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.43,0:44:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It took effort, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.07,0:44:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but visiting the congregation \Nahead of time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.51,0:44:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was well worth it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.51,0:44:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! \NWe already have friends here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.95,0:44:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Unpacking seemed to never end, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.52,0:44:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one thing \Nthat we all promised ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.02,0:44:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at family worship \Nwas that we would not let \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.69,0:44:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our move affect \Nour spiritual routine.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.63,0:44:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anyone seen my ties? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.20,0:44:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Found them!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.47,0:44:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We planned that we \Nwouldn’t let anything stop us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.01,0:44:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from going to the meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.01,0:44:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The ministry is very different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.48,0:45:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had to adapt \Nand learn new techniques. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.38,0:45:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers and sisters \Nare different too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.72,0:45:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s important not to focus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.59,0:45:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on negative comparisons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.56,0:45:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, be positive.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.50,0:45:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,During this transition, \Nit is especially important to be sensitive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.63,0:45:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to our spiritual needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Family worship is vital. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.31,0:45:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping spiritually grounded \Nthrough such a big transition isn’t easy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.38,0:45:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,especially with a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.41,0:45:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It took a lot of time \Nand energy to care for our needs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.42,0:45:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,not just spiritually, \Nbut emotionally too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.62,0:45:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Planning ahead, \Nlike the discreet man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.69,0:45:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,helped our family \Nto stay spiritually grounded.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.96,0:45:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a spiritually strong family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.10,0:45:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,prepares us also \Nfor other changes in life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.84,0:46:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you are in your teens \Nand you’re starting to notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.54,0:46:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,those of the opposite sex. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.88,0:46:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Such emotions are natural \Nand are part of growing up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.88,0:46:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you’re not old enough \Nto get married, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.48,0:46:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you need \Nto keep in mind? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.75,0:46:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This young sister \Nmade wise decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.06,0:46:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the loving help \Nof her parents.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.84,0:46:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhh, yours?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.84,0:46:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NThanks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.27,0:46:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re Lily, right?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.94,0:46:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NAnd you’re Sean.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.95,0:46:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NI’ve seen you around. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.41,0:46:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You play good basketball.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.48,0:46:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. \NSo do you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.78,0:46:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you want \Nto hang out sometime?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.79,0:46:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.59,0:46:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Lily, \Nand I sorta had this problem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.26,0:47:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a boy named Sean \Nthat recently moved to our school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.24,0:47:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I’m not supposed \Nto like anyone who is not a Witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.51,0:47:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The trouble was, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.98,0:47:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he is a Witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.58,0:47:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sean and his family \Nmoved into our congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.68,0:47:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more I saw of him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.62,0:47:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the more I liked him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.62,0:47:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“My strength is exhausted \Nbecause of my sighing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.46,0:47:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“If only I knew \Nwhere to find God! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.29,0:47:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“I would go \Nto his place of dwelling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.29,0:47:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would present my . . .”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.98,0:47:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.98,0:47:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“I had a problem.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.59,0:47:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day I see \Ncouples my age at school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.56,0:48:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, they look happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.00,0:48:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I wanted \Nthat happiness too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.21,0:48:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents noticed my problem too \Nand talked about it that night.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.82,0:48:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And pretty soon \NI didn’t feel alone anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.22,0:48:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, my mom invited me \Nto go with her to run an errand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.16,0:48:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterward, \Nwe went to a little café. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.56,0:48:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked me \Nhow things were going. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.60,0:48:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, \NI didn’t want to tell her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.14,0:48:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but she made me \Nfeel really comfortable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.07,0:48:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I told her \Nmy feelings for Sean, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.44,0:48:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,expecting her \Nto think bad of me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.94,0:48:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But she didn’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.95,0:48:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you’re feeling \Nis natural, Lily. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.95,0:48:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember having these same feelings \Nwhen I was your age too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.95,0:49:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.22,0:49:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.56,0:49:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s just how Jehovah \Ncreated us, Honey. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.39,0:49:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And because he created us, \Nhe knows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.83,0:49:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the best way \Nfor us to be happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.30,0:49:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s all he wants for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.03,0:49:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s all Daddy \Nand I want for you too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.50,0:49:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t scold me; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.51,0:49:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn’t make me \Nfeel embarrassed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.51,0:49:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And most importantly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.51,0:49:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,she didn’t seem to be in a rush.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.61,0:49:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom wasn’t the only one \Nhelping me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.95,0:49:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad was preparing \Nto help me with my problem too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.82,0:49:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That evening, \Nwe had family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.76,0:49:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And once again,\Nthey just let me talk. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.10,0:49:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They told me I didn’t have \Nto hold back, so I didn’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.63,0:49:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don’t know what to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.37,0:49:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Lily, thank you \Nfor telling us how you feel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.97,0:49:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you something: \NWhy do you think Jehovah created us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.94,0:49:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with these natural feelings \Ntoward the opposite sex?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.35,0:50:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So that one day a man \Nand woman could marry.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.75,0:50:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.88,0:50:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, a good marriage \Nis like two skaters on the ice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.49,0:50:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful performance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.76,0:50:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,can seem effortless, \Nbut is it really?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.69,0:50:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.83,0:50:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No one would even \Nattempt that without practice, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.10,0:50:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a capable partner, \Nor the right kind of guidance, right?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.97,0:50:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.24,0:50:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s the same \Nwith a good marriage, Sweetie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.71,0:50:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t just happen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.71,0:50:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It too depends \Non a good partner, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.75,0:50:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinated effort, \Nbut most importantly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.82,0:50:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,wise counsel from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.45,0:50:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.49,0:50:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,could you please turn with me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.49,0:50:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to Psalm 32:8 \Nand read that for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.33,0:50:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.33,0:50:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N“I will give you insight \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.73,0:50:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“and instruct you \Nin the way you should go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.07,0:50:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I will give you advice \Nwith my eye upon you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.11,0:51:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Lily, Jehovah loves us very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.18,0:51:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we listen to him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.21,0:51:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll make good decisions in our life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.88,0:51:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with absolutely no regrets.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.12,0:51:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked some more, \Nand then I got some homework. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.32,0:51:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad gave me some articles \Nhe printed out for me to read, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.56,0:51:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so I did. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.23,0:51:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I read the words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.73,0:51:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and started meditating on them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.73,0:51:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized something.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.60,0:51:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By holding off dating a little longer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.67,0:51:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn’t missing out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.98,0:51:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, I was preparing myself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.91,0:51:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use the time now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.22,0:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to focus on something \Nmuch more important\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.65,0:51:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—my relationship with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.66,0:51:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I could also gain Christian qualities \Nand experience that will help me later \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.89,0:51:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if I ever do get married.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.90,0:52:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A strong spiritual upbringing \Ncan truly be a protection for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.91,0:52:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when young \Nbut also strengthens us as adults.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.28,0:52:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Erich Frost \Nwas a young man in Germany \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.15,0:52:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who set a good example \Nin making wise decisions early in life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.09,0:52:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He was born in 1900, \Nbaptized 23 years later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.03,0:52:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and entered \Nthe full-time ministry in 1928. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.76,0:52:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Not long after, he was put in charge \Nof the underground work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.60,0:52:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the persecuted \NWitnesses of Jehovah in Germany, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.34,0:52:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,caring well for that assignment \Nfor eight months \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.87,0:52:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,until he was incarcerated. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.21,0:52:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In this archived audio recording, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.05,0:52:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you will hear the fascinating experience \Nof how Brother Frost \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.25,0:52:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,composed a Kingdom melody \Nin the middle of Sachsenhausen\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.12,0:52:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—a Nazi concentration camp.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.13,0:53:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I always had the desire \Nto compose music.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.77,0:53:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,As everybody knows, \Nwe had the hardest work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.80,0:53:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffered the hardest \Nin the concentration camps. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.67,0:53:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We were starved, \Nthe labor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.14,0:53:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,exceeded our strength, \Nand the harassment was often unbearable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.19,0:53:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as usual, I wanted to find \Na way to build up the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.06,0:53:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We had such a fine unity \Nthere in the Sachsenhausen camp. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.07,0:53:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt moved \Nto compose a song \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.40,0:53:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we could sing together \Nfor our mutual encouragement.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.81,0:53:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Every morning we marched \Nto the construction site \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.55,0:53:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of a sewage plant \Nin Oranienburg. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.99,0:54:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Our labor group \Nconsisted of about 40 brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.09,0:54:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,under the strict watch of the SS.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.20,0:54:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,While marching, \Nmy mind went back and forth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.84,0:54:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and “Bum Bam Badam \NBam Tarambambamba.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.68,0:54:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And gradually, \Na melody formed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.68,0:54:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how the music \Nwas developed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.22,0:54:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But how could the verses \Nenter the camp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.55,0:54:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,without being able \Nto write them down? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.56,0:54:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a few brothers \Nwho helped me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.76,0:54:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I repeated the first verse \Nto one of them until he knew it by heart, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.86,0:54:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,either while marching or while driving \Nthe wheelbarrow at work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.33,0:54:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I told the second verse \Nto another brother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.60,0:54:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,still to others the third \Nand the fourth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.67,0:54:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In the evening, I asked \Neach of the brothers to recite his verse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.55,0:55:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how the song came to life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.55,0:55:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the mornings, \Nwhen the 40 of us were marching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.75,0:55:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,through the streets of Oranienburg, \Nwe already felt worn out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.26,0:55:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When one started humming \Nthat melody, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.13,0:55:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire labor group \Ntrembled with excitement. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.56,0:55:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We had to control ourselves \Nto not break out in loud singing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.97,0:55:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That would have been dangerous, \Nof course. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.27,0:55:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They would have brought us \Nback to the camp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.27,0:55:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and severely punished us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.77,0:56:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As we sat together in the evenings \Nand someone started humming that melody,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.48,0:56:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,quite a number of us \Nsang along, and we rejoiced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.28,0:56:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Our eyes were shining. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.48,0:56:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This gave us \Nnew courage and hope.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.76,0:56:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We also had evenings of worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.29,0:56:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Talks were given, and we had copies \Nof The Watchtower that we studied together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.96,0:57:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were able to have \Nsome real times of peace \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.37,0:57:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and special encouragement \Nand felt uplifted by that song.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.56,0:58:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Frost, \Nwho was one of the anointed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.90,0:58:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,finished \Nhis earthly course in 1987. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.70,0:58:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War II \Nand nine years of imprisonment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.84,0:58:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he served as the overseer \Nof our branch office \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.58,0:58:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in Germany for ten years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.58,0:58:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This was before \Nthe arrangement was instituted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.98,0:58:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of having a Branch Committee \Noversee the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.55,0:58:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The very descriptive paintings \Nthat you saw in this segment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.19,0:58:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,were painted by a brother \Nwho was imprisoned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.72,0:58:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in a concentration camp \Nsimilar to the one Brother Frost was in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.40,0:58:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m sure \Nyou recognized the song. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.53,0:58:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can find it in our songbook, \Nthough the tune is a little different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.94,0:58:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When Brother Frost found out \Nthat his song had been included in it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.94,0:58:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,he was overjoyed \Nand said, “My clumsy lyrics \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.81,0:58:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,were transformed \Ninto three wonderful verses.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.02,0:58:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If you turn to song 17 \Nin your songbook, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.29,0:59:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll find the song \Noriginally composed by Brother Frost\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.12,0:59:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,—“Forward, You Witnesses!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.33,0:59:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Brother Frost, \Nwe want to do our best \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.06,0:59:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand our ministry \Nfor Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.90,0:59:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One way of doing that \Nis by learning a language. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.57,0:59:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In this music video, \Npay close attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.01,0:59:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the blessings that resulted \Nfrom this couple’s heartfelt desire \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.54,0:59:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve \Nin the foreign-language field.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.07,0:59:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be contemplating,\N‘Should I make the move?’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.44,1:00:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayerfully meditating,\N‘Jehovah, what should I do?’\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.35,1:00:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s just take a moment\NAnd try to help you decide.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.03,1:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Cause if you step on over,\NYou’ll be so happy you tried!\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.44,1:00:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta step on over\NAnd leave your worries behind.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.55,1:00:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Cause when you step on over,\NYou will be blessed if you try, oh.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.09,1:00:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Step on over.\NStep on over that Macedonia line!\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.80,1:01:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The preaching work is amazing,\NWith overwhelming success.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.61,1:01:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be appreciating\NHow strangers give you their best.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.35,1:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will draw even closer\NTo Jehovah each day.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.80,1:01:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Cause he will always be there\NTo help you learn every step of the way.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.44,1:01:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta step on over\NAnd leave your worries behind.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.81,1:01:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Cause when you step on over,\NOh, the treasures you’ll find.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.65,1:01:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’re thinking it over\NAnd wondering if it’s right, oh.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.50,1:02:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta step on over.\NYou will be blessed if you try, oh.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.00,1:02:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Step on over.\NStep on over.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.31,1:02:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta step on over that Macedonia line!\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.83,1:02:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nsome of the blessings \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.96,1:02:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this couple enjoyed as the result \Nof learning a new language? \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.03,1:02:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only were they able \Nto expand their ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.97,1:02:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and show their love for neighbor \Nbut they also spent a lot of time together \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.57,1:02:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as a couple, reaching the goal \Nof learning a language as a family. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.61,1:02:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,By working hard to build up \Nand protect our family spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.48,1:02:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we can all take part \Nin glorifying Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.69,1:02:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—the One “to whom every family \N. . . owes its name.”\N
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.69,1:03:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll also enjoy a Bethel morning worship \Nthat is now available \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.93,1:03:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,on Video on Demand. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.93,1:03:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It ties very well into the theme \Nof this month’s program. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.60,1:03:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The video is entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.67,1:03:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Practice Godly Devotion\Nin Our Own Household’ \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.21,1:03:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and is presented \Nby Brother David Schafer, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.88,1:03:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a helper \Nto the Teaching Committee.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.21,1:03:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have more \Nin store for you.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.62,1:03:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re also pleased to announce \Nthe release of a new brochure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.15,1:03:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled \NAnswers to 10 Questions Young People Ask.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.89,1:03:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The content of this 32-page, \Nfull-color brochure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.53,1:03:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on articles \Nin Awake! and the two volumes \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.53,1:03:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Questions Young People Ask\N—Answers That Work, as well as \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.00,1:03:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the “Young People Ask” articles \Non the jw.org website. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.74,1:03:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This new brochure \Nwill be particularly helpful \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.41,1:03:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who speak a language \Nin which that material is not available. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.02,1:04:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, all young people \Ncan benefit from this new brochure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.62,1:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because the original articles \Nhave been updated and rewritten.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.63,1:04:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Each section of the brochure \Naddresses one question. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.10,1:04:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After stating the question, \Nthe section begins with a pointed statement \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.97,1:04:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,under the feature \N“Why It Matters,” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.84,1:04:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,letting the reader know \Nwhy that question is relevant. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.71,1:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, a “What Would You Do?” \Nscenario is presented, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.25,1:04:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,putting the reader \Nin a hypothetical situation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.45,1:04:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,related to the topic. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.59,1:04:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After discussing various principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.52,1:04:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Scriptural advice \Ndirects the reader to the best answers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.33,1:04:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for that particular question.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.86,1:04:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The 10 Questions brochure \Nis interactive, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.97,1:04:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing the reader \Nto write responses \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.47,1:04:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to the various questions presented. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.87,1:04:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The final topic, \N“How Can the Bible Help Me?,” \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.21,1:04:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is designed to invite readers \Nwho are not Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.35,1:05:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept a Bible study. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.48,1:05:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The brochure \Nmakes numerous references \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.48,1:05:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the jw.org website \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.82,1:05:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and directs readers to more information \Nthat can be found there. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.09,1:05:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the brochure \Nis designed in such a way \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.89,1:05:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that young people can be comfortable \Nsharing it with their peers \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.03,1:05:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and with others in the ministry.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.57,1:05:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This brochure \Nis already approved for translation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.51,1:05:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,into 324 languages. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.08,1:05:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of these languages, \N223 do not produce Awake! \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.08,1:05:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and 262 have not produced \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.75,1:05:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the Young People Ask books. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.75,1:05:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So we expect that Answers \Nto 10 Questions Young People Ask \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.89,1:05:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,will help \Nmany more youths benefit \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.63,1:05:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Bible’s practical wisdom.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.70,1:05:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Following this program, \Ndigital formats of the brochure \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.50,1:05:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,will become available \Non the jw.org website, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.97,1:06:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the JW Library app, \Nand on Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.91,1:06:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as they are produced \Nin each language. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.54,1:06:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, printed copies \Nof the brochure can be requested \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.05,1:06:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,through your congregation \Nat the conclusion of this program.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.72,1:06:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we finish, \Nwe’d like to share \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.72,1:06:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,this postcard from the city \Nof L’viv, in Ukraine. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.13,1:06:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The city has approximately \N800,000 inhabitants and is surrounded \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.07,1:06:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by beautiful forests. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.07,1:06:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But L’viv is also the home of 5,000 \Nof our dear brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.07,1:06:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the 49 congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.44,1:06:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in L’viv \Nis the Topolna Tsentralnyi Congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.65,1:06:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This congregation \Nhas 107 publishers, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.02,1:06:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,including 42 regular pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.02,1:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, during the month of August, \N70 percent of them took part \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.16,1:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in some form of pioneer service, \Ndespite the fact that this congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.00,1:07:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,has [one of] the smallest \Nterritories in the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.37,1:07:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Public witnessing using carts \Nhas proven very effective, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.37,1:07:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the publishers also cover \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.71,1:07:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,remote territories \Nin small villages outside the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.38,1:07:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The publishers \Nof the Topolna Tsentralnyi Congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.11,1:07:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,send their warm Christian love \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.65,1:07:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of us worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.35,1:07:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.69,1:07:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from Brooklyn, New York.\N
